":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring enum definitions**\\n\\nI’m wondering if I need to define an enum. Can Circe generic derive Scala 3 enums? It seems like testing the enum with specific cases might be a good idea. I think circe-generic_3 probably supports Mirror for enums, but I need to check that. There’s a lot to consider here, so I’ll have to look into it further to ensure I get the right setup and usage.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_fidilZLKvQmIzuiFjKi8zN4n|fc_0ca3540bff41a2df016a28d52715d8819595418864d5125f3a", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "metadata/io.circe/circe-generic_3/0.14.12/reachability-metadata.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 531, "output": 1581, "cacheRead": 19456, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21568, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781060866056, "responseId": "resp_0ca3540bff41a2df016a28d502681081959b19f24eb445fd65"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_fidilZLKvQmIzuiFjKi8zN4n|fc_0ca3540bff41a2df016a28d52715d8819595418864d5125f3a", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781060903466}]}
